## 6. `[VeloxProperty]` / `[VeloxCommand]` — Collaboration with the Agent system

Although `[VeloxProperty]` and `[VeloxCommand]` are essentially MVVM source generators, they work closely with the Agent system:

### 6.1 `[VeloxProperty]` — Agent readable and writable properties

```csharp
[VeloxProperty]                              // ← Generate complete MVVM property
[AgentContext(AgentLanguages.English, "Output slot (sender)")]
public partial SlotViewModel OutputSlot { get; set; }
```

**Agent Tool Dependencies:**
- `ListProperties` — list all `[VeloxProperty]` attributes, read the `[AgentContext]` description
- `GetProperty` — read property value
- `SetProperty` / `PatchProperties` — write property values (subject to `ComponentPatcher` safety rule constraints)

### 6.2 `[VeloxCommand]` — Commands callable by Agent

```csharp
[VeloxCommand]                               // ← Generate IVeloxCommand
[AgentContext(AgentLanguages.English, "Starts the workflow: broadcasts SeedPayload")]
private async Task OpenWorkflow(object? parameters, CancellationToken ct)
{
    // ...
}
```

**Agent Tool Dependencies:**
- `ListCommands` — Lists all commands and `[AgentContext]` descriptions
- `ExecuteCommand` — calls the command (parameters specify type via [AgentCommandParameter])

### 6.3 Commands with Verification

```csharp
[VeloxCommand(canValidate: true)]
private Task Minus(object? sender, CancellationToken ct)
{
    Index--;
    return Task.CompletedTask;
}

// This partial method must be implemented:
private partial bool CanExecuteMinusCommand(object? parameter) => _index > 0;
```

Agent checks `CanExecute` before calling the command, and will not execute if it returns `false`.

